taste is preserved - in a way. chinese brandy (白兰地) is excellent value, about the same price as grape wine or baijiu, and generally far more palatable than either. a ¥16-20 local brandy is not a ¥200+ imported brand-name cognac, but it is close enough that you should only buy the cognac if money doesn't matter. expats debate the relative merits of brandies from french-owned louis wann [40], chinese brand changyu [41], and several others. all are drinkable. the chinese are also great fans of various supposedly medicinal liquors, which usually contain exotic herbs and/or animal parts. some of these 